.\" termin.al-name: login
.\" termin.al-usage: login
.\" termin.al-summary: Authenticate with GitHub.
.TH LOGIN 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
login \- Authenticate with GitHub.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
login
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Opens the GitHub authentication flow in a popup. Any GitHub identity receives viewer capability; the configured numeric owner identity receives owner and CV capabilities.
.SH OUTPUT
On success, prints the authenticated GitHub login and capability. Authentication failures use one generic diagnostic.
.SH FAILURES
Arguments are rejected. A blocked popup, invalid or expired correlation, unavailable configuration, failed token exchange, or five-second completion timeout reports
.BR "Authentication failed." .
.SH NOTES
Tokens are never placed in terminal output, browser-visible URLs or popup messages. The offline demo changes only its synthetic in-memory session and performs no OAuth or network operation.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ login
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
logout(1), whoami(1), cv(1)
